Problem Statement

Write a program that displays the message "Hello, World!" on the screen.

Description

The objective of this problem is to help beginners become familiar with the basic structure of a program in their chosen programming language. This includes:

Understanding how to write the minimal code required to output text.
Learning the correct syntax for printing messages to the console.
Gaining confidence in setting up and running a program successfully.
Input Format

No input is required for this program.
Output Format

The program should output the following message exactly:

Hello, World!

Sample Output 0

Hello, World!

SOLUTION:
#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    printf("Hello, World!");
    return 0;
}
